headline: T. Rowe Price’s Fixed Income ETF Launch Could Be a Game Changer for TROW
summary: Earlier this month, T. Rowe Price announced the launch of four new active fixed income ETFs, including three expanding its municipal bond offerings and a multi-sector income fund, all now trading on NASDAQ and bringing the firm's total active ETF lineup to 28 funds. The expanded ETF lineup highlights T. Rowe Price's efforts to diversify its product range and attract new client segments, reflecting ongoing innovation in response to evolving investor preferences.
